Lab Name: Low-Level Logic Flaw

Category: Business Logic Vulnerabilities

Difficulty: Practitioner

Objective: Exploit an arithmetic flaw caused by improper handling of numeric values.

Vulnerability Description

The application performs arithmetic operations without properly validating user-supplied numeric input. By submitting unexpected values, an attacker can manipulate calculations and bypass intended business restrictions.

Exploitation Summary

The purchase request was modified by supplying unexpected numeric values, causing the application's calculations to behave incorrectly. This allowed the purchase to proceed under conditions that should have been rejected.

Impact

Attackers can manipulate application logic to obtain products at incorrect prices or bypass financial controls, potentially resulting in revenue loss.

Key Takeaway

Applications should validate all numeric input and safely handle arithmetic operations to prevent logic flaws such as integer overflow, underflow, or unexpected calculation results.